cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the optimization of traffic offloading in cellular networks, which is a problem related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization techniques and power control, which are related to information theory and signal processing, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of offloading on mobile data cost and interference control, which are related to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC), respectively.
